1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,440
(Announcement for the 5th Round of Open Pick Voting Results)

2
00:00:02,440 --> 00:00:04,110
(A: Wanna One's Fashion Film)

3
00:00:04,110 --> 00:00:06,480
(B: Wanna One's Get Ready With Me)

4
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:09,210
(The photo shoot day of a famous fashion magazine)

5
00:00:09,710 --> 00:00:12,620
(Wanna One is getting dolled up for the photo shoot.)

6
00:00:12,880 --> 00:00:13,890
(Reducing the swelling is a must!)

7
00:00:13,890 --> 00:00:15,290
(Ji Sung is also getting his makeup done.)

8
00:00:15,450 --> 00:00:16,890
We're filming WANNA ONE GO today.

9
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:19,220
The staff fed us...

10
00:00:19,320 --> 00:00:21,960
tteokbokki for breakfast and fishcakes on a stick.

11
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:24,900
Then they brought us here for this photo shoot.

12
00:00:25,030 --> 00:00:27,370
Who on earth eats tteokbokki for breakfast before a photo shoot?

13
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:31,070
(He enjoyed the food more than anyone.)

14
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:32,400
I never know what they're up to.

15
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,810
I need to be on my guard.

16
00:00:34,340 --> 00:00:36,340
Seriously. I can never tell what we'll do on this show.

17
00:00:36,440 --> 00:00:37,440
(He's also caught off guard.)

18
00:00:37,740 --> 00:00:40,450
Usually, the day before the photo shoot,

19
00:00:40,450 --> 00:00:41,650
I don't eat anything.

20
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:42,710
I go for a run.

21
00:00:42,710 --> 00:00:45,220
It's my first time doing a photo shoot...

22
00:00:45,650 --> 00:00:46,750
without any preparation.

23
00:00:46,990 --> 00:00:49,350
What do you think about wearing contact lenses?

24
00:00:49,490 --> 00:00:50,560
- Contact lenses? - Yes.

25
00:00:50,660 --> 00:00:51,860
It's been a long time since I wore them.

26
00:00:51,860 --> 00:00:53,060
You can't put them on, right?

27
00:00:53,060 --> 00:00:54,330
My eyes are too small for them.

28
00:00:54,330 --> 00:00:55,390
Gosh, no.

29
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:58,600
I think I can't put them on because my eyes are too small.

30
00:00:58,900 --> 00:01:00,100
- Dae Hwi. - Yes?

31
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:02,330
Doesn't it feel like the old days when we used to perform together?

32
00:01:02,330 --> 00:01:05,200
Focus only on how grateful you are and feel these precious moments.

33
00:01:05,740 --> 00:01:06,970
- Okay? - Amen.

34
00:01:06,970 --> 00:01:08,710
So there are no regrets later.

35
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:09,910
I'm over the moon right now.

36
00:01:09,910 --> 00:01:11,740
Thoroughly enjoy this happy moment.

37
00:01:11,940 --> 00:01:13,410
I said I was happy.

38
00:01:14,080 --> 00:01:16,080
Seriously. It feels like I'm dreaming.

39
00:01:16,310 --> 00:01:18,380
The last time we were together was at the 2021 MAMA Awards.

40
00:01:18,550 --> 00:01:20,920
It's our first time doing a group project since then.

41
00:01:20,920 --> 00:01:22,750
I'm used to doing things by myself these days.

42
00:01:22,750 --> 00:01:24,660
But we're doing a photo shoot together after a long time.

43
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,060
I'm sure we'll have fun together.

44
00:01:28,430 --> 00:01:30,800
(Once everyone gets ready, the group photo shoot begins.)

45
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:33,470
We'll say our slogan on the count of three.

46
00:01:33,470 --> 00:01:34,470
- Okay. - Yes.

47
00:01:35,130 --> 00:01:36,630
- All I wanna do, Wanna One. - All I wanna do, Wanna One.

48
00:01:37,340 --> 00:01:38,740
(The polite winking cutie bows too.)

49
00:01:38,740 --> 00:01:41,240
- Why did you bow? - Why did you bow?

50
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:42,970
It's a habit of mine.

51
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:45,610
"Hello. We're Wanna One." It just comes naturally.

52
00:01:45,610 --> 00:01:46,740
We'll look at the camera on three?

53
00:01:46,740 --> 00:01:47,980
- Yes. I got it. - Yes.

54
00:01:47,980 --> 00:01:49,710
- One, two, three. - You like that.

55
00:01:49,710 --> 00:01:51,120
- All I wanna do, Wanna One. - All I wanna do, Wanna One.

56
00:01:51,250 --> 00:01:53,080
(Nailing it perfectly)

57
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:54,650
Go.

58
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:57,290
(A dance party begins out of the blue.)

59
00:01:57,290 --> 00:02:00,330
(In a trance)

60
00:02:00,330 --> 00:02:02,630
(Their crazy random dance moves continue.)

61
00:02:02,630 --> 00:02:03,930
(The rebellion of office workers)

62
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:06,760
Can all of you try headbanging?

63
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:11,070
(In one moment, they look like the coolest group.)

64
00:02:11,070 --> 00:02:13,240
(Then they become playful in a matter of seconds.)

65
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:15,210
(The group photo shoot is over.)

66
00:02:16,770 --> 00:02:18,910
I can pull off any outfit.

67
00:02:19,210 --> 00:02:20,580
Dae Hwi does look good in any outfit.

68
00:02:20,580 --> 00:02:22,250
His shoulder lines look really good.

69
00:02:22,250 --> 00:02:23,410
Oh, my.

70
00:02:23,410 --> 00:02:24,580
And he has long legs.

71
00:02:24,580 --> 00:02:25,720
Oh, my.

72
00:02:25,720 --> 00:02:26,850
He also has a small face.

73
00:02:26,850 --> 00:02:29,190
Oh, my. I should compliment Jjaeni too.

74
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:30,260
His outfits complement his shape.

75
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:31,260
Jjaeni...

76
00:02:32,890 --> 00:02:34,560
- Hey. - Hold on.

77
00:02:42,670 --> 00:02:44,500
(WANNA ONE GO: Back to Base, Final Episode)

78
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:47,340
All right. Let's go in.

79
00:02:49,970 --> 00:02:51,480
Will there be breakfast?

80
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:53,380
We need to eat breakfast as soon as we go in.

81
00:02:53,380 --> 00:02:54,980
I've been waiting for today.

82
00:02:54,980 --> 00:02:56,650
I wanted to see you guys.

83
00:02:56,710 --> 00:02:59,380
(I've been waiting for today)

84
00:02:59,480 --> 00:03:00,720
Wanna Base!

85
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:05,290
(They enter the base for the final time.)

86
00:03:05,290 --> 00:03:06,660
- It's dark in here. - It's dark.

87
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,930
- Hey. It's dark! - Turn the light on for us.

88
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,160
- It's dark in here. - It's dark.

89
00:03:11,260 --> 00:03:13,700
- Turn the light on for us. - Hey. It's dark!

90
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:15,130
- Why is the light off? - Why is it so dark here?

91
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,130
Hey!

92
00:03:16,330 --> 00:03:17,570
(Whatever. I'll jump in.)

93
00:03:18,670 --> 00:03:20,100
- A parachute. - Hold on.

94
00:03:20,100 --> 00:03:21,210
Get your parachute on.

95
00:03:21,210 --> 00:03:23,140
- Three, two, one. Jump. - Get your parachute on.

96
00:03:23,140 --> 00:03:24,580
(The chirpy birdie flies.)

97
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:25,810
Jump.

98
00:03:25,880 --> 00:03:26,880
(Diving in)

99
00:03:26,880 --> 00:03:28,510
(Surprised)

100
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:30,520
That must hurt a bit.

101
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:32,280
- Gosh, they're so young. - They're full of energy.

102
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:34,590
They're so energetic this morning.

103
00:03:35,820 --> 00:03:37,320
- What? - Hey!

104
00:03:37,690 --> 00:03:39,690
- Hey, we're doomed. - What's this? Hey.

105
00:03:39,690 --> 00:03:41,630
- Hey. - We're so doomed. Hurry.

106
00:03:41,630 --> 00:03:43,430
- What? I'm curious. - What is it?

107
00:03:43,630 --> 00:03:44,900
Hurry up! I'm serious.

108
00:03:44,900 --> 00:03:46,200
- What is it? - I guess it changed.

109
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:47,330
(They quickly enter out of curiosity.)

110
00:03:47,330 --> 00:03:48,400
- What's going on? - Hurry.

111
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:50,570
- What? It's under construction. - There's construction going on.

112
00:03:50,570 --> 00:03:52,240
- They're closing it down. - What is this?

113
00:03:52,240 --> 00:03:53,470
How come our base is ruined?

114
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:55,840
(Wanna Base is ruined?)

115
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,410
- Why... - This...

116
00:03:57,410 --> 00:03:59,380
(The do-not-enter tapes are put up across every room.)

117
00:03:59,780 --> 00:04:00,780
(The tapes...)

118
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:02,010
(are everywhere.)

119
00:04:02,010 --> 00:04:03,650
(Wanna Base is under construction. It's not ruined.)

120
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:04,720
- Hurry. - Hurry up.

121
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:06,050
How come it's all blocked?

122
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,490
Why is it blocked?

123
00:04:07,920 --> 00:04:08,990
I'm getting the chills.

124
00:04:09,350 --> 00:04:10,660
How come our base is ruined?

125
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:11,660
Hey, why...

126
00:04:11,660 --> 00:04:12,760
I see something over here.

127
00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:14,430
Let's look at it together. Come.

128
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,660
Everyone, come here. It's an announcement.

129
00:04:16,660 --> 00:04:18,600
- What is it? - It's an announcement!

130
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:21,930
We were just away for a few days. Are there really spiderwebs here?

131
00:04:22,170 --> 00:04:23,230
(Euratgotcha...)

132
00:04:23,230 --> 00:04:25,300
(is covered with spiderwebs.)

133
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:27,810
There's a smaller Euratgotcha.

134
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,940
Hey. Look. Let me read this out loud.

135
00:04:29,940 --> 00:04:32,340
"Welcome to your final day in Wanna Base."

136
00:04:32,340 --> 00:04:35,780
"You will set out on a trip while granting Wannables' requests."

137
00:04:36,110 --> 00:04:37,780
"It's the Wanna List Day."

138
00:04:37,780 --> 00:04:39,320
- What? We're going on a trip. - I see.

139
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,520
- We're going on a trip? - We're traveling.

140
00:04:40,890 --> 00:04:42,350
(Already getting excited)

141
00:04:42,450 --> 00:04:44,090
"The Wanna List Euratgotcha..."

142
00:04:44,090 --> 00:04:47,090
"only has requests from Wannables."

143
00:04:47,090 --> 00:04:49,030
(Wait, Wannables?)

144
00:04:49,030 --> 00:04:52,060
I see. Yes. The show was collecting requests.

145
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,000
(Wannables' anticipated content collected over 4 days)

146
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:58,070
(Wannables' enthusiastic participation resulted in...)

147
00:04:58,070 --> 00:05:00,870
(about 5,000 requests for the Wanna List.)

148
00:05:01,210 --> 00:05:03,210
"Turn the Wanna List Euratgotcha."

149
00:05:03,210 --> 00:05:05,640
"And set out to your first destination."

150
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:06,640
That sounds great.

151
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:07,880
(I love traveling.)

152
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:09,950
We just got here, but we'll leave right away?

153
00:05:10,250 --> 00:05:12,350
Guys, do you see these six balls here?

154
00:05:12,350 --> 00:05:13,580
- Yes. - Yes.

155
00:05:13,580 --> 00:05:15,650
They look pretty cool because of the gold color.

156
00:05:15,650 --> 00:05:17,560
- I figured it out. - What is it?

157
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,660
Only six of us completed our mission last time.

158
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:20,660
- Wait! - Wait!

159
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:24,630
(The Don't Get Caught and Go Mission was held at the photo shoot.)

160
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:26,700
(There had been tears...)

161
00:05:26,700 --> 00:05:28,370
(and a fist.)

162
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:31,470
(All kinds of conspiracies...)

163
00:05:31,470 --> 00:05:34,610
(and twists unfolded at the shoot.)

164
00:05:34,970 --> 00:05:37,680
(In the end, 6 of them completed the mission.)

165
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,210
(The golden balls for the successful members)

166
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:43,050
- Hey! That's right! - There was a mission.

167
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:44,450
- We did the mission. - It must be a huge benefit!

168
00:05:44,450 --> 00:05:47,090
- Yes! We got a benefit. - What is it?

169
00:05:47,190 --> 00:05:48,590
(The failed members quietly gather together.)

170
00:05:48,590 --> 00:05:49,590
We...

171
00:05:49,590 --> 00:05:50,590
(The failed members quietly gather together.)

172
00:05:50,690 --> 00:05:52,590
It doesn't apply to me. So whatever.

173
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:54,730
(They're not strawberries.)

174
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:56,330
- Are you in the same boat with us? - None for you?

175
00:05:56,330 --> 00:05:58,100
- Great. - Sung Woon threw my strawberries.

176
00:05:58,860 --> 00:06:01,700
Come on. It's a pie in the sky.

177
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:03,630
This is small, but it doesn't break.

178
00:06:03,630 --> 00:06:04,640
- My gosh. - What is it?

179
00:06:04,740 --> 00:06:06,300
My goodness. This is amazing. Hey.

180
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:07,570
Don't tell them.

181
00:06:07,570 --> 00:06:08,870
- Come here. Don't tell them. - Hey.

182
00:06:08,870 --> 00:06:10,540
- Let's not tell them. - Let's not tell them.

183
00:06:10,540 --> 00:06:12,240
(A complete divide)

184
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,550
- Gosh, this is great. - This is great.

185
00:06:14,650 --> 00:06:15,980
(The sad sight of their backs)

186
00:06:16,150 --> 00:06:17,950
(You guys don't have this, do you?)

187
00:06:18,150 --> 00:06:19,880
(Rubbing it in their faces)

188
00:06:22,150 --> 00:06:24,020
- He's so annoying. - What is it?

189
00:06:24,420 --> 00:06:26,090
I'm sorry. But I read Jin Young's.

190
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:30,060
(Jin Young was trying to crack open the golden ball.)

191
00:06:30,700 --> 00:06:32,430
- What is it? - Hey.

192
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:33,630
(He read it.)

193
00:06:34,130 --> 00:06:35,930
(For the benefit of completing the mission,)

194
00:06:35,930 --> 00:06:38,300
(they can pick a member who will wait on their hand and foot.)

195
00:06:38,770 --> 00:06:40,910
(I can't believe we may have to wait on their hand and foot.)

196
00:06:41,240 --> 00:06:43,640
We can pair up and then pick one. One, two, three, four, five...

197
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:45,740
I thought we were one. We're Wanna One.

198
00:06:46,040 --> 00:06:47,910
You're making us feel alienated.

199
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,780
- He'll keep... - Never.

200
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,180
He'll keep doing that.

201
00:06:51,180 --> 00:06:52,980
- I don't want him. - He's...

202
00:06:52,980 --> 00:06:53,990
What's going on?

203
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:55,690
What is it?

204
00:06:55,790 --> 00:06:57,290
(How dare you try to take a peek?)

205
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:01,330
No, sir! Go away.

206
00:07:01,330 --> 00:07:03,530
(Pushed away)

207
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:05,700
(Jjaeni fails to be one of them in the end.)

208
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,060
Why don't we try Euratgotcha?

209
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:08,570
Let's get one.

210
00:07:08,570 --> 00:07:10,030
But why are you doing it?

211
00:07:10,230 --> 00:07:11,470
Did you just get angry at us?

212
00:07:11,470 --> 00:07:13,140
- What did you say? - Let's go with Woo Jin.

213
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,210
- Let's pick Woo Jin. - Let's go with Woo Jin.

214
00:07:15,210 --> 00:07:16,310
Let's go with Woo Jin.

215
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:18,240
- We should go with Woo Jin. - Wait. Hey.

216
00:07:18,240 --> 00:07:19,940
- Why did you yell at him? - Wait.

217
00:07:19,940 --> 00:07:21,050
- What's wrong with you? - Right.

218
00:07:21,050 --> 00:07:22,150
Guys, can you believe him?

219
00:07:22,150 --> 00:07:23,550
- Are you all right? - I'm so angry.

220
00:07:23,550 --> 00:07:25,020
- Are you all right? - No, I'm not.

221
00:07:25,750 --> 00:07:27,720
- Hey. - He's cast out.

222
00:07:27,920 --> 00:07:29,190
- A while ago... - What?

223
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:31,490
- You're not with them. - Hold on.

224
00:07:31,490 --> 00:07:32,490
You said we were in the same boat.

225
00:07:32,490 --> 00:07:33,590
(Watch your mouth in front of them.)

226
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,690
(I'm so glad I completed my mission.)

227
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,160
(After getting scolded pretty badly, Woo Jin plays Euratgotcha.)

228
00:07:38,530 --> 00:07:40,030
- Draw a good one. - We'll look forward to it, Woo Jin.

229
00:07:40,430 --> 00:07:41,970
(He turned it.)

230
00:07:41,970 --> 00:07:43,470
When did he do that? That was fast.

231
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:46,070
What is it?

232
00:07:46,070 --> 00:07:47,410
(What's the first activity Woo Jin drew?)

233
00:07:48,470 --> 00:07:49,970
Woo Jin, read it out loud.

234
00:07:50,510 --> 00:07:51,680
"I'd like to see them..."

235
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:54,710
"play a survival game together."

236
00:07:55,050 --> 00:07:56,050
- My gosh. - What?

237
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:57,920
- Like the one with guns? - What?

238
00:07:57,920 --> 00:07:59,880
People who served in the military have an upper hand.

239
00:07:59,880 --> 00:08:01,450
Then hold on.

240
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:03,860
- Hey, you need to go over there. - Right?

241
00:08:03,860 --> 00:08:05,090
- Go. - Go over there.

242
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:06,760
- You should join us. - Come here.

243
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:07,930
- You'll take me, right? - Nice.

244
00:08:07,930 --> 00:08:08,960
Hey, have you...

245
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:09,990
- worked with guns in dramas? - I...

246
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,960
I didn't serve yet. So I should be here.

247
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:13,100
Go over there if you haven't served yet.

248
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,230
(Grouping by military experience)

249
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:17,030
What kind of survival game is it?

250
00:08:17,030 --> 00:08:19,140
But it didn't clarify what kind of game it was.

251
00:08:19,140 --> 00:08:21,040
Well, it won't be the survival show we were on like "Produce 101."

252
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:22,570
It just says they want to watch us play a survival game.

253
00:08:22,570 --> 00:08:24,540
- We have to leave in ten minutes. - What?

254
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:25,540
- What? - Right now?

255
00:08:25,540 --> 00:08:26,940
- What? - Right now?

256
00:08:27,110 --> 00:08:28,750
Ten minutes... Hold on.

257
00:08:29,350 --> 00:08:30,410
Grab food.

258
00:08:30,410 --> 00:08:32,380
We have ten minutes. Pack food now.

259
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:33,750
Already?

260
