777
00:25:21,690 --> 00:25:25,900
(He hides behind the wall and quickly moves in the back.)

778
00:25:26,130 --> 00:25:29,100
(A cool play to ambush Wise Hwang from behind)

779
00:25:29,930 --> 00:25:31,640
(Peekaboo)

780
00:25:31,640 --> 00:25:32,740
(Wise Hwang of Perfect Aim)

781
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:34,140
(Screaming)

782
00:25:34,140 --> 00:25:35,470
(Wise Hwang is out, unable to put up a fight.)

783
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:37,470
(That's sad.)

784
00:25:37,940 --> 00:25:40,780
(He returns to HQ after scoring consecutive points.)

785
00:25:40,780 --> 00:25:41,950
You're winning with the score...

786
00:25:41,950 --> 00:25:43,110
- of 8 to 3. - Okay.

787
00:25:43,110 --> 00:25:44,920
(Team JYGS is leading thanks to his performance.)

788
00:25:45,350 --> 00:25:48,050
(Current score, Perfect Aim: 3, JYGS: 8)

789
00:25:48,290 --> 00:25:50,690
(The battlefield is too scary for Wise Hwang.)

790
00:25:50,690 --> 00:25:51,690
(Min Hyun)

791
00:25:51,690 --> 00:25:52,860
(Taking cover in the helicopter)

792
00:25:53,090 --> 00:25:54,690
(He carefully hides in the helicopter's rear section.)

793
00:25:54,860 --> 00:25:56,460
(At that moment, Ji Hoon,)

794
00:25:56,460 --> 00:25:58,960
(a jaguar, is running toward the helicopter's front section.)

795
00:25:59,930 --> 00:26:01,560
(The two of them are at it again.)

796
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:03,170
(The scaredy-cat emperor fires at him wildly.)

797
00:26:03,970 --> 00:26:05,900
(He's shot!)

798
00:26:06,140 --> 00:26:07,270
(Winking Seong Jae is out as he steps back.)

799
00:26:07,540 --> 00:26:09,610
(Wise Hwang did it.)

800
00:26:09,810 --> 00:26:11,840
(Smiling)

801
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:15,510
(After hunting jaguar, he's brimming with confidence.)

802
00:26:18,210 --> 00:26:19,580
(Peekaboo)

803
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:23,890
(He positions himself there and starts shooting.)

804
00:26:24,750 --> 00:26:26,260
Gosh, where did that come from?

805
00:26:26,320 --> 00:26:27,990
(Bae Bae who only looked ahead is out.)

806
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:29,130
(Wise Hwang of Perfect Aim)

807
00:26:29,130 --> 00:26:30,130
(I got him.)

808
00:26:30,290 --> 00:26:32,000
(Feeling proud)

809
00:26:32,160 --> 00:26:33,930
(Private First Class Hwi of JYGS)

810
00:26:33,930 --> 00:26:36,670
(Wise Hwang of Perfect Aim)

811
00:26:37,030 --> 00:26:38,840
(He scores 3 points in a row as he eliminates Dae Hwi.)

812
00:26:38,970 --> 00:26:39,970
My gosh.

813
00:26:40,140 --> 00:26:41,600
He was hiding in there.

814
00:26:42,070 --> 00:26:45,580
(He has leveled up to Emperor Sniper.)

815
00:26:45,580 --> 00:26:46,910
(Meanwhile,)

816
00:26:47,280 --> 00:26:49,780
(Sergeant Jjaen emphasized on taking cover.)

817
00:26:49,950 --> 00:26:50,950
(Jae Hwan)

818
00:26:50,950 --> 00:26:52,780
(Getting ready to shoot behind a wooden box)

819
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:55,520
(He hides in the perfect spot where he can observe his enemies.)

820
00:26:55,990 --> 00:26:57,990
(I'll put an end to this battle now.)

821
00:26:58,220 --> 00:26:59,920
(Spotting his target right away)

822
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:00,960
Let's go.

823
00:27:01,730 --> 00:27:02,730
(Winking Seong Jae of JYGS)

824
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:05,030
(He's out as soon as he comes out.)

825
00:27:05,060 --> 00:27:06,060
(Sergeant Jjaen of Perfect Aim)

826
00:27:06,060 --> 00:27:07,400
(Giggling)

827
00:27:07,930 --> 00:27:09,030
Bye.

828
00:27:09,870 --> 00:27:12,240
(He spots Private First Class Hwi after eliminating one opponent.)

829
00:27:12,440 --> 00:27:13,840
(Clueless of the ambush, he keeps firing forward.)

830
00:27:14,470 --> 00:27:16,570
(After failing to look around, Private First Class Hwi is out.)

831
00:27:16,670 --> 00:27:17,670
(Jin Young)

832
00:27:17,670 --> 00:27:18,840
Gosh, what was that?

833
00:27:19,440 --> 00:27:20,910
(Bae Bae is out.)

834
00:27:21,340 --> 00:27:22,550
(Brimming with confidence)

835
00:27:22,750 --> 00:27:23,910
Yes, baby!

836
00:27:23,910 --> 00:27:25,180
Come on, baby!

837
00:27:26,020 --> 00:27:28,920
We got them surrounded. Surround them!

838
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:30,150
(Team Perfect Aim begins surrounding their base.)

839
00:27:30,150 --> 00:27:31,250
Surround them!

840
00:27:31,620 --> 00:27:33,790
(Surrounding their opponents all around)

841
00:27:33,890 --> 00:27:35,760
- You have to get out there. - They're coming over.

842
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:36,960
They're coming over here.

843
00:27:36,960 --> 00:27:38,430
(Winking Seong Jae of JYGS)

844
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:40,660
(Remember what I said? It's not over until it is.)

845
00:27:40,900 --> 00:27:43,770
(He stays close to the wall and approaches them covertly.)

846
00:27:43,930 --> 00:27:46,540
(The jaguar is waiting for his prey with bated breath.)

847
00:27:46,800 --> 00:27:49,540
(A bunny is running in clueless of what awaits him.)

848
00:27:49,640 --> 00:27:52,010
(Winking Seong Jae of JYGS)

849
00:27:52,180 --> 00:27:53,180
(Ji Hoon, Ji Sung)

850
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:54,780
(Welcome.)

851
00:27:54,880 --> 00:27:55,880
(Shooting Jirung of Perfect Aim)

852
00:27:55,880 --> 00:27:58,580
(The ambush is successful, and Jirung is out.)

853
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,450
(Ji Sung, Ji Hoon)

854
00:28:00,450 --> 00:28:03,320
(He's attacking Jirung who's on his way back to HQ.)

855
00:28:06,420 --> 00:28:09,330
Hey, help me! Hold on.

856
00:28:09,330 --> 00:28:12,330
(A hostage situation unfolds out of the blue.)

857
00:28:12,930 --> 00:28:15,370
What's going on? What?

858
00:28:15,630 --> 00:28:18,370
(Oh, no. Poor Ji Sung.)

859
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:21,200
(Winking Seong Jae is getting close to the enemy camp.)

860
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,870
- Why... - Don't move!

861
00:28:22,870 --> 00:28:23,970
Why are you...

862
00:28:23,970 --> 00:28:26,140
(Unstoppable)

863
00:28:26,840 --> 00:28:28,340
Hold on!

864
00:28:28,340 --> 00:28:30,310
Hey, don't shoot!

865
00:28:30,510 --> 00:28:32,020
(The sad shout of the oldest member echoes through the battlefield.)

866
00:28:32,380 --> 00:28:33,750
Don't shoot, you punks!

867
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:35,120
(Crying Jirung)

868
00:28:35,350 --> 00:28:37,050
(Winking Seong Jae is ambushing them while hiding behind Jirung.)

869
00:28:37,050 --> 00:28:38,120
(Perfect Aim Ong of Perfect Aim)

870
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:40,060
(Perfect Aim Ong is out and fails to rescue Ji Sung.)

871
00:28:40,060 --> 00:28:41,560
(Emperor Sniper of Perfect Aim)

872
00:28:41,560 --> 00:28:42,890
(The emperor is out with a toothy smile.)

873
00:28:43,530 --> 00:28:45,800
- Don't shoot. - Hey. Darn it.

874
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,430
Why are you shooting at me?

875
00:28:47,730 --> 00:28:49,700
Don't shoot.

876
00:28:49,700 --> 00:28:51,870
(Running away after securing the middle section)

877
00:28:51,870 --> 00:28:52,900
(Dashing)

878
00:28:52,900 --> 00:28:53,940
(Winking Seong Jae of JYGS)

879
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,740
(This is so much fun.)

880
00:28:55,740 --> 00:28:56,740
(Released Jirung of Perfect Aim)

881
00:28:56,740 --> 00:28:58,740
(Drained)

882
00:28:59,180 --> 00:29:01,180
(Perfect Aim is in the lead.)

883
00:29:01,180 --> 00:29:02,310
I'm out of ammunition.

884
00:29:02,310 --> 00:29:03,710
(Woo Jin at JYGS's HQ)

885
00:29:03,880 --> 00:29:06,720
(Captain Birdie is guarding HQ at all costs.)

886
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:08,720
They're in the lead now!

887
00:29:09,450 --> 00:29:11,050
(They're in the lead now?)

888
00:29:12,290 --> 00:29:14,460
(His attack power gets boosted instantly.)

889
00:29:15,060 --> 00:29:18,560
(He starts attacking them while dominating the battlefield.)

890
00:29:18,700 --> 00:29:19,700
(Sergeant Jjaen of Perfect Aim)

891
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:21,800
(Sergeant Jjaen is out.)

892
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:24,570
(Startled)

893
00:29:25,500 --> 00:29:26,740
I got shot in the head.

894
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:27,840
(Giggling)

895
00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,840
(Woo Jin, Sung Woon)

896
00:29:31,040 --> 00:29:32,680
(Firing at his next target, Captain Sung Woon)

897
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:34,140
(Captain Birdie of JYGS, Captain Sung Woon of Perfect Aim)

898
00:29:34,140 --> 00:29:36,410
(Bullseye)

899
00:29:36,410 --> 00:29:37,810
(He eliminates Perfect Aim's captain with a single shot.)

900
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:40,150
(Smiling)

901
00:29:40,420 --> 00:29:42,050
(Perfect Aim Ong is approaching for revenge.)

902
00:29:42,250 --> 00:29:43,420
(Shooting with one hand)

903
00:29:44,020 --> 00:29:45,190
(Another perfect shot)

904
00:29:45,490 --> 00:29:48,390
(This is the class of a captain.)

905
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,030
Forty-five seconds!

906
00:29:50,960 --> 00:29:53,060
Forty-five seconds!

907
00:29:54,030 --> 00:29:57,030
We got them surrounded. Let's surround them.

908
00:29:57,030 --> 00:29:58,130
(Perfect Aim tries the pincer tactic again.)

909
00:29:58,640 --> 00:30:00,770
(Launching the final attack)

910
00:30:00,900 --> 00:30:02,110
(Team JYGS is completely surrounded.)

911
00:30:02,110 --> 00:30:03,640
We have to get out there.

912
00:30:03,740 --> 00:30:06,310
(Team JYGS fights to the end.)

913
00:30:06,310 --> 00:30:08,880
(Winking Seong Jae of JYGS)

914
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:11,110
(At this rate, we're going to lose.)

915
00:30:11,180 --> 00:30:12,550
I must go around the back.

916
00:30:12,720 --> 00:30:14,080
(The last attack of the ace, Winking Seong Jae)

917
00:30:14,250 --> 00:30:16,320
(This is his actual running speed.)

918
00:30:16,550 --> 00:30:17,750
Come around the back!

919
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:20,960
(Winking Seong Jae runs at an incredible speed.)

920
00:30:21,090 --> 00:30:22,190
Come around the back!

921
00:30:22,730 --> 00:30:25,630
(Ji Sung, Ji Hoon)

922
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:26,930
(Shooting Jirung of Perfect Aim)

923
00:30:26,930 --> 00:30:28,630
(The last showdown between Ji Sung and Ji Hoon)

924
00:30:28,630 --> 00:30:30,670
(Ji Hoon, Ji Sung)

925
00:30:30,930 --> 00:30:34,340
(Who's the final victor?)

926
00:30:34,500 --> 00:30:37,840
(Winking Seong Jae of JYGS)

927
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:41,210
(Ji Sung was faster.)

928
00:30:41,380 --> 00:30:44,150
(Disappointed)

929
00:30:45,220 --> 00:30:46,520
The battle is over.

930
00:30:48,250 --> 00:30:49,520
We won.

931
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:50,650
- We won? - Look.

932
00:30:50,650 --> 00:30:52,160
- Nice. - Yes!

933
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:53,890
- Nice! - We won!

934
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:55,490
Gosh, we lost.

935
00:30:55,490 --> 00:30:56,630
We lost by four points.

936
00:30:57,390 --> 00:30:59,560
The winning team is...

937
00:30:59,960 --> 00:31:01,000
Perfect Aim!

938
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:02,330
(Hooray for Perfect Aim!)

939
00:31:02,330 --> 00:31:03,600
(Utterly excited)

940
00:31:04,330 --> 00:31:05,340
We lost...

941
00:31:05,340 --> 00:31:06,440
We lost, but we did well.

942
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:08,040
We were 1-man short. But we lost only by 4 points.

943
00:31:08,040 --> 00:31:09,110
- We still did well. - Right.

944
00:31:09,340 --> 00:31:11,510
Guys, did you feel the difference?

945
00:31:11,510 --> 00:31:13,840
Guys, do you see now? You'll be like us once you serve.

946
00:31:13,840 --> 00:31:15,040
- All right. - You guys can do it too.

947
00:31:15,040 --> 00:31:17,650
If the difference is only four points between us...

948
00:31:17,650 --> 00:31:20,120
But those four points decided the winning and losing teams.

949
00:31:20,120 --> 00:31:21,180
Right.

950
00:31:21,620 --> 00:31:24,550
All right. I'll announce the individual scores.

951
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:26,560
Whoever used fewer bullets while scoring points...

952
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:27,560
will win first place.

953
00:31:27,790 --> 00:31:30,090
- I'm curious. - The one with the highest accuracy.

954
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:32,560
- First place goes to... - In the middle.

955
00:31:32,660 --> 00:31:35,700
(Tension at its max)

956
00:31:36,630 --> 00:31:38,070
Yoon Ji Sung of Perfect Aim.

957
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,240
(Surprised)

958
00:31:39,400 --> 00:31:40,740
Come on.

959
00:31:40,740 --> 00:31:42,410
Are you for real?

960
00:31:43,340 --> 00:31:44,410
- Really? - What?

961
00:31:44,410 --> 00:31:45,540
- Hold on. - Stop lying.

962
00:31:45,540 --> 00:31:47,680
- Is that for shooting at us? - No. I'm serious.

963
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:49,410
- Really? - Come on.

964
00:31:49,650 --> 00:31:51,510
Did you guys count the ones when he fired at us?

965
00:31:51,510 --> 00:31:52,650
They count too?

966
00:31:52,650 --> 00:31:55,590
Scoring a lot of points is important and all.

967
00:31:55,590 --> 00:31:57,590
But using a lot of bullets would lower the accuracy rate.

968
00:31:57,590 --> 00:31:59,090
- Are you for real? - It's for real.

969
00:31:59,090 --> 00:32:00,160
We weren't supposed to use a lot of bullets.

970
00:32:00,160 --> 00:32:01,220
We weren't. We had to score...

971
00:32:01,220 --> 00:32:02,230
- with a single shot. - Yes.

972
00:32:02,860 --> 00:32:05,500
(Unlike the other members who fired their guns nonstop,)

973
00:32:06,030 --> 00:32:11,800
(Jirung stayed calm and was careful with each shot.)

974
00:32:11,970 --> 00:32:13,600
Here's what I think.

975
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:15,070
It must come from the years of his experience...

976
00:32:15,070 --> 00:32:16,740
on reserve military training.

977
00:32:16,740 --> 00:32:17,740
Right.

978
00:32:17,740 --> 00:32:20,280
(The best sniper of Wanna One, Yoon Ji Sung)

979
00:32:20,410 --> 00:32:21,980
- All right. Second place. - Gosh.

980
00:32:21,980 --> 00:32:23,180
(Announcing 2nd place for individual scores)

981
00:32:23,180 --> 00:32:25,110
(Feeling desperate to be 2nd)

982
00:32:25,350 --> 00:32:27,680
Second place goes to Ha Sung Woon of Perfect Aim.

983
00:32:27,680 --> 00:32:29,390
(Ha Sung Woon, ranked 2nd for individual scores)

984
00:32:31,620 --> 00:32:33,060
(I'm Captain Sung Woon.)

985
00:32:33,460 --> 00:32:35,260
He scored 744 points.

986
00:32:36,090 --> 00:32:37,290
Third place.

987
00:32:37,730 --> 00:32:39,930
(No one from Team JYGS has been called yet.)

988
00:32:40,130 --> 00:32:42,070
- It's from Team JYGS. - I wonder who it is.

989
00:32:42,130 --> 00:32:44,100
(Is it Captain Birdie who turned into a raptor?)

990
00:32:44,870 --> 00:32:46,170
- Is it Ji Hoon? - I bet it's him.

991
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:47,940
(Pointing)

992
00:32:47,940 --> 00:32:48,940
- Is it Jin Young? - It's...

993
00:32:48,940 --> 00:32:49,940
Is it me?

994
00:32:50,170 --> 00:32:51,240
- It's... - Is it Jin Young?

995
00:32:51,240 --> 00:32:52,910
Park Ji Hoon!

996
00:32:52,910 --> 00:32:54,780
- I knew it. - It's as expected.

997
00:32:54,780 --> 00:32:56,310
- He's the military cook. - Ji Hoon.

998
00:32:56,750 --> 00:32:57,910
Here's the fourth place.

999
00:32:58,250 --> 00:32:59,520
It goes to Kim Jae Hwan of Perfect Aim.

1000
00:32:59,520 --> 00:33:00,680
(Kim Jae Hwan, ranked 4th for individual scores)

1001
00:33:00,720 --> 00:33:02,490
Fifth place goes to Ong Seong Wu of Perfect Aim.

1002
00:33:02,490 --> 00:33:04,120
(Ong Seong Wu, ranked 5th for individual scores)

1003
00:33:04,290 --> 00:33:06,460
Sixth place goes to Hwang Min Hyun of Perfect Aim.

1004
00:33:07,620 --> 00:33:09,230
I'm glad I scored higher than Min Hyun.

1005
00:33:09,230 --> 00:33:10,330
(He's unbelievable.)

1006
00:33:10,490 --> 00:33:11,890
- Well... - What about me?

1007
00:33:11,890 --> 00:33:14,660
When will the three of them be called?

1008
00:33:14,660 --> 00:33:17,030
Seventh, eighth, and ninth places remain now.

1009
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,270
The last three places.

1010
00:33:18,270 --> 00:33:19,440
It's so humiliating.

1011
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:20,440
All right.

1012
00:33:20,870 --> 00:33:22,040
This is unexpected.

1013
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:23,070
- Really? - It's an unexpected result.

1014
00:33:23,070 --> 00:33:24,810
Then I didn't come last.

1015
00:33:25,380 --> 00:33:27,010
Hold on a second. A timeout.

1016
00:33:27,010 --> 00:33:28,680
- Why is Woo Jin's score so low? - All right.

1017
00:33:28,680 --> 00:33:29,780
I might have come last.

1018
00:33:29,780 --> 00:33:31,880
I used a lot of bullets.

1019
00:33:32,080 --> 00:33:33,450
- Step forward. - Step forward.

1020
00:33:33,450 --> 00:33:34,680
- Come on. - This is...

1021
00:33:34,680 --> 00:33:36,090
more important than announcing first place.

1022
00:33:36,090 --> 00:33:37,720
I'll announce the seventh place.

1023
00:33:37,720 --> 00:33:38,960
From Team JYGS...

1024
00:33:38,960 --> 00:33:39,960
Is it me?

1025
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:42,430
(Could it be me?)

1026
00:33:43,190 --> 00:33:44,460
I think I scored the lowest.

1027
00:33:44,460 --> 00:33:46,160
- No way. - It's Bae Jin Young!

1028
00:33:48,130 --> 00:33:49,130
- Is it me? - It's Bae Jin Young!

1029
00:33:49,130 --> 00:33:50,570
- Me? - It's Bae Jin Young.

1030
00:33:51,100 --> 00:33:52,370
(Bae Jin Young, ranked 7th for individual scores)

1031
00:33:52,370 --> 00:33:53,600
- I won seventh place? - Jin Young.

1032
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:55,370
- Hold on. - Jin Young.

1033
00:33:55,370 --> 00:33:57,240
- But Woo Jin... - Jin Young.

1034
00:33:57,670 --> 00:33:58,980
- But Woo Jin... - Jin Young.

1035
00:33:58,980 --> 00:34:00,810
(Woo Jin isn't here.)

1036
00:34:00,810 --> 00:34:03,280
- I'm not surprised to be here. - Look.

1037
00:34:03,280 --> 00:34:05,180
- But this is quite shocking. - It's between Dae Hwi and him?

1038
00:34:05,310 --> 00:34:07,150
- Woo Jin did his absolute best. - Hey.

1039
00:34:07,720 --> 00:34:08,820
I'll announce...

1040
00:34:09,090 --> 00:34:12,020
the member in ninth place, the absolute last place.

1041
00:34:12,260 --> 00:34:14,990
(Utterly...)

1042
00:34:14,990 --> 00:34:17,430
(intrigued)

1043
00:34:17,630 --> 00:34:20,560
(Who scored the lowest as an individual player?)

1044
00:34:22,270 --> 00:34:23,700
I'll announce it after 60 seconds.

1045
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,800
(He wanted to try it once.)

1046
00:34:26,140 --> 00:34:27,170
I'll announce it after 60 seconds.

1047
00:34:27,170 --> 00:34:28,400
(Unable to breathe)

1048
00:34:29,370 --> 00:34:30,710
(Bursting into laughter)

1049
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:33,480
(This familiar line brings back nightmares.)

1050
00:34:33,480 --> 00:34:34,610
It's a nightmare.

1051
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:37,080
(He's checked out.)

1052
00:34:37,550 --> 00:34:38,950
I'll announce ninth place.

1053
00:34:39,550 --> 00:34:41,780
(9th place for individual scores)

1054
00:34:41,780 --> 00:34:43,150
Park Woo Jin!

1055
00:34:44,790 --> 00:34:47,360
(I can't believe this!)

1056
00:34:47,860 --> 00:34:51,290
(Last place)

1057
00:34:51,290 --> 00:34:52,600
I did better than you.

1058
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,630
(Captain Birdie lowers his head.)

1059
00:34:54,660 --> 00:34:55,900
I did better than you. Okay?

1060
00:34:55,900 --> 00:34:57,670
- This is crazy. - I didn't think he'd rank last.

1061
00:34:57,670 --> 00:34:58,730
Really?

1062
00:34:59,270 --> 00:35:01,600
(Captain Birdie fired the most shots out of everyone.)

1063
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,970
(He used 4 times as many bullets as Jirung.)

1064
00:35:04,510 --> 00:35:06,810
- I didn't think he'd rank last. - I thought he'd do well.

1065
00:35:06,810 --> 00:35:09,180
He did well. He just used too many bullets.

1066
00:35:10,350 --> 00:35:11,710
- Woo Jin. - Let's stop here.

1067
00:35:11,710 --> 00:35:13,920
This survival game made him sulk.

1068
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:15,120
(Ji Sung: 822 points, Sung Woon: 744 points, Ji Hoon: 702 points,)

1069
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:16,390
(Jae Hwan: 676 points, Seong Wu: 655 points, Min Hyun: 644 points,)

1070
00:35:16,390 --> 00:35:17,650
(Jin Young: 523 points, Dae Hwi: 483 points, Woo Jin: 466 points)

1071
00:35:18,220 --> 00:35:19,690
- Next... - Next?

1072
00:35:19,690 --> 00:35:20,920
There's more?

1073
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,330
You need to fulfill the Wanna List.

1074
00:35:22,330 --> 00:35:24,060
You'll play Wanna List Euratgotcha.

1075
00:35:24,060 --> 00:35:25,290
Okay. Let's play it.

1076
00:35:25,290 --> 00:35:26,700
Last place, I'll give you a chance.

1077
00:35:26,700 --> 00:35:28,160
Yes. Woo Jin should do it since he was ranked last.

1078
00:35:28,160 --> 00:35:29,230
(This is sad.)

1079
00:35:29,230 --> 00:35:30,570
Play Wanna List Euratgotcha.

1080
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:33,370
Euratgotcha.

1081
00:35:34,140 --> 00:35:35,440
(His shout drains their energy just by listening to it.)

1082
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:37,140
Could you do it with more energy?

1083
00:35:37,140 --> 00:35:38,370
- He's sulking. - He's sulking?

1084
00:35:38,370 --> 00:35:42,080
I'll keep this energy level until I get some happy news.

1085
00:35:42,680 --> 00:35:43,780
(Coming up next)

1086
00:35:43,780 --> 00:35:47,850
(He's back with full of energy and excitement.)

1087
00:35:48,080 --> 00:35:49,620
Okay. Read it.

1088
00:35:49,820 --> 00:35:50,890
What is it?

1089
00:35:51,420 --> 00:35:53,620
I see, "Wanna One."

1090
00:35:54,520 --> 00:35:55,960
(That makes sense. We're Wanna One.)

1091
00:35:56,090 --> 00:35:57,160
I see, "sky."

1092
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,190
- "Sky?" - What?

1093
00:35:58,360 --> 00:35:59,360
What?

1094
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,900
I'll read it now.

1095
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:02,000
(What's the second activity on the Wanna List?)

1096
00:36:02,230 --> 00:36:05,500
Wanna One, fly in a cool manner!

1097
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:06,870
- Gosh, is it bungee jumping? - What?

1098
00:36:06,870 --> 00:36:07,900
- Is it bungee jumping? - Bungee jumping?

1099
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:10,340
There's more.

1100
00:36:10,340 --> 00:36:12,540
"Only two members will try it."

1101
00:36:13,310 --> 00:36:15,480
- "No more, no less." That's it. - That's all?

1102
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:17,910
- I want to do it! - That's all.

1103
00:36:18,450 --> 00:36:21,480
I have to try this. I really want to do it.

1104
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:23,220
- Let Ji Hoon try it. - Okay.

1105
00:36:23,220 --> 00:36:24,290
Thank you.

1106
00:36:24,290 --> 00:36:25,320
(I did it.)

1107
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:26,620
(I want to fly too.)

1108
00:36:26,860 --> 00:36:28,420
We need one more person. Who wants to do it?

1109
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:29,430
Me!

1110
00:36:29,830 --> 00:36:31,690
(Kitty Min Hyun loses his chance to volunteer.)

1111
00:36:32,730 --> 00:36:34,630
(I want to try it too.)

1112
00:36:34,900 --> 00:36:38,470
Okay. Ji Hoon and Seong Wu will go and fly.

1113
00:36:38,770 --> 00:36:39,870
The sky masters.

1114
00:36:39,870 --> 00:36:40,870
(Saluting)

1115
00:36:40,970 --> 00:36:44,040
- What will the rest of them do? - It's crazy.

1116
00:36:44,070 --> 00:36:45,640
They'll draw one more capsule.

1117
00:36:45,710 --> 00:36:47,140
- Shall we? - Okay.

1118
00:36:47,140 --> 00:36:48,340
Can I try it?

1119
00:36:48,340 --> 00:36:49,510
Go ahead, Min Hyun.

1120
00:36:50,050 --> 00:36:51,480
- I go with the green one. - Euratgotcha.

1121
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,620
What is it?

1122
00:36:53,220 --> 00:36:54,650
Is it a good one or a bad one?

1123
00:36:54,650 --> 00:36:57,320
Personally, I love doing this.

1124
00:36:57,320 --> 00:36:59,290
- I bet it's cleaning. - It's cleaning.

1125
00:36:59,290 --> 00:37:01,460
(Bursting into laughter)

1126
00:37:01,860 --> 00:37:03,030
(He fails to hold back his laughter.)

1127
00:37:03,030 --> 00:37:05,230
What if we have to go back to the base and clean?

1128
00:37:05,230 --> 00:37:06,460
Is it demolishing Wanna Base?

1129
00:37:07,260 --> 00:37:08,300
It's a demolition job?

1130
00:37:08,300 --> 00:37:09,970
I'll announce it.

1131
00:37:09,970 --> 00:37:12,000
(What's the third activity on the Wanna List?)

1132
00:37:12,130 --> 00:37:13,570
"I want to see you..."

1133
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:16,110
"have a good time at a vacation rental."

1134
00:37:16,110 --> 00:37:18,210
(We love you, Wannables!)

1135
00:37:18,310 --> 00:37:20,610
"The seaside vacation rental has facilities..."

1136
00:37:20,610 --> 00:37:22,680
"for jokgu and a campfire area."

1137
00:37:22,710 --> 00:37:23,780
- Really? - Yes.

1138
00:37:23,850 --> 00:37:24,850
- Okay. - Let's go.

1139
00:37:24,850 --> 00:37:27,280
That's what Seong Wu wanted to do the most.

1140
00:37:27,280 --> 00:37:28,280
(Oh, you fool...)

1141
00:37:28,280 --> 00:37:29,350
(Ong a moment ago)

1142
00:37:30,690 --> 00:37:32,220
(Really?)

1143
00:37:32,590 --> 00:37:34,590
(A mocking performance)

1144
00:37:34,690 --> 00:37:37,030
(Min Hyun lightens up as they get to tease Ong.)

1145
00:37:37,630 --> 00:37:39,400
(Oh, poor Seong Wu.)

1146
00:37:39,830 --> 00:37:42,870
(A sad flyer with a chipped wing)

1147
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:45,500
- Let's get going. - Let's go.

1148
00:37:45,900 --> 00:37:47,270
I thought other members...

1149
00:37:47,270 --> 00:37:49,370
would do something exciting as well.

1150
00:37:49,440 --> 00:37:51,040
(The member who placed last isn't interested.)

1151
00:37:51,040 --> 00:37:53,710
Let's move to the next location.

1152
00:37:53,710 --> 00:37:54,710
Okay.

1153
00:37:54,810 --> 00:37:56,080
(Team Fly to the Sky)

1154
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:59,220
(Team Relax at the Vacation Rental)

1155
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:02,080
(Min Hyun boards the van for the winning team.)

1156
00:38:02,250 --> 00:38:04,190
You traveled very comfortably earlier.

1157
00:38:04,190 --> 00:38:05,860
Yes, it was really nice.

1158
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:06,960
Is everyone here?

1159
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:09,490
This van is nice.

1160
00:38:09,490 --> 00:38:11,960
(Baby Bae sets up the massage chair for Woo Jin.)

1161
00:38:12,660 --> 00:38:13,830
What's this?

1162
00:38:13,930 --> 00:38:15,400
- It has a massage function. - It has a massage function.

1163
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:16,870
(Sparrow gets surprised by the latest technology.)

1164
00:38:17,330 --> 00:38:19,040
(Wanna One travels comfortably to the vacation rental.)

1165
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:20,600
I'm hungry.

1166
00:38:20,600 --> 00:38:22,910
I'm hungry after shooting.

1167
00:38:22,910 --> 00:38:25,270
Shall we visit a rest area if we can?

1168
00:38:25,270 --> 00:38:26,280
- Good idea. - I'd like that.

1169
00:38:26,280 --> 00:38:28,040
We received money, right?

1170
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:29,810
(Here it is.)

1171
00:38:30,050 --> 00:38:32,180
What about Jae Hwan and Min Hyun?

1172
00:38:32,420 --> 00:38:33,750
Come on.

1173
00:38:33,980 --> 00:38:35,280
- Sung Woon. - Yes?

1174
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,620
Can't we go to the rest area?

1175
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:37,890
- The rest area? - Yes.

1176
00:38:37,890 --> 00:38:40,090
What's the use of going? You don't have money anyway.

1177
00:38:40,090 --> 00:38:41,120
(Disappointed)

1178
00:38:41,320 --> 00:38:42,460
Ji Sung.

1179
00:38:42,460 --> 00:38:44,230
I want to eat walnut cake.

1180
00:38:44,230 --> 00:38:45,960
- Do you want to eat walnut cake? - Yes.

1181
00:38:45,960 --> 00:38:48,760
You guys need to put on a show to eat that.

1182
00:38:48,930 --> 00:38:50,270
(A show?)

1183
00:38:50,270 --> 00:38:53,170
People will go insane once Sung Woon gets off the van.

1184
00:38:53,170 --> 00:38:55,470
- He shouldn't get off. - Why not?

1185
00:38:55,470 --> 00:38:57,540
Everyone will recognize you and rush over.

1186
00:38:57,540 --> 00:38:58,640
Do you crave it that much?

1187
00:38:58,640 --> 00:38:59,910
It isn't like that.

1188
00:39:00,210 --> 00:39:01,580
I thought we were one.

1189
00:39:01,910 --> 00:39:03,510
Why do you have so many complaints?

1190
00:39:03,510 --> 00:39:04,910
- What? - You have many complaints.

1191
00:39:04,910 --> 00:39:06,880
I was talking to myself.

1192
00:39:06,880 --> 00:39:08,420
- Please keep it down. - Okay.

1193
00:39:08,420 --> 00:39:10,350
I'm sad.

1194
00:39:11,050 --> 00:39:13,360
Can we really not eat anything?

1195
00:39:13,360 --> 00:39:15,090
- Do we need to play a game? - If you want to eat,

1196
00:39:15,090 --> 00:39:16,390
show us a cute act or something.

1197
00:39:16,390 --> 00:39:17,390
I mean...

1198
00:39:17,390 --> 00:39:18,430
(Showing off his dumpling-like cheeks)

1199
00:39:20,660 --> 00:39:22,470
(Here is the cute act you've ordered.)

1200
00:39:22,470 --> 00:39:24,270
- It'll have to be something else. - I know. That won't do.

1201
00:39:24,270 --> 00:39:25,770
(Here is another cute act you've ordered.)

1202
00:39:25,970 --> 00:39:27,570
(But he sounds like a water deer.)

1203
00:39:27,570 --> 00:39:29,170
(A wild water deer appeared!)

1204
00:39:30,240 --> 00:39:31,770
- What? - Is the door open?

1205
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:33,180
Did someone open the door?

1206
00:39:33,580 --> 00:39:35,280
Ji Sung.

1207
00:39:35,280 --> 00:39:37,010
(After the water deer, they unleash all sorts of animals.)

1208
00:39:37,410 --> 00:39:40,150
(An animal farm opens.)

1209
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:41,880
- Hey. - Shall we buy them food?

1210
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:43,950
- Let's do that. - Sure.

1211
00:39:44,190 --> 00:39:47,220
- Okay. - Sure. They're cute.

1212
00:39:47,220 --> 00:39:48,890
- Let's look, since we have money. - Okay.

1213
00:39:48,890 --> 00:39:50,460
Sung Woon, should Woo Jin get off the van or not?

1214
00:39:50,460 --> 00:39:52,660
- Woo Jin can stay here. - He can stay in the van.

1215
00:39:52,660 --> 00:39:55,230
Only Jae Hwan and Min Hyun acted cute.

1216
00:39:55,230 --> 00:39:56,470
We'll buy them snacks.

1217
00:39:57,030 --> 00:39:59,870
(Sweet Hwang takes care of the younger member.)

1218
00:40:00,500 --> 00:40:01,800
Let's go.

1219
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,840
We're at a rest area.

1220
00:40:04,410 --> 00:40:06,040
This place has everything.

1221
00:40:06,580 --> 00:40:08,110
Hey, strawberry mochi sounds tasty.

1222
00:40:08,280 --> 00:40:09,880
Shall we eat one each?

1223
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:11,480
Let's eat a mochi.

1224
00:40:11,480 --> 00:40:13,320
- Thank you. - Thank you.

1225
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:15,650
(The next snack is cold ice cream.)

1226
00:40:15,750 --> 00:40:17,490
Let's give Min Hyun a mochi.

1227
00:40:17,490 --> 00:40:18,690
- Okay. - Jae Hwan,

1228
00:40:18,690 --> 00:40:21,060
do you want a mochi or ice cream? Choose one.

1229
00:40:21,060 --> 00:40:22,220
I'll take this one.

1230
00:40:22,220 --> 00:40:23,690
- Ice cream? - Yes, ice cream.

1231
00:40:23,690 --> 00:40:26,100
Ji Sung, Jin Young wants a corn dog. Please give him money.

1232
00:40:26,130 --> 00:40:27,500
- Here. - Let's go and buy it.

1233
00:40:27,500 --> 00:40:28,800
I'll go with you.

1234
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,230
(A sparrow follows them.)

1235
00:40:31,070 --> 00:40:33,200
- Jin Young, what will you eat? - I want to take a look.

1236
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:36,140
I'll take a boneless chicken skewer. Do you want one as well?

1237
00:40:36,140 --> 00:40:37,140
Okay.

1238
00:40:37,140 --> 00:40:38,610
(Thief Woo Jin easily acquires a skewer.)

1239
00:40:38,640 --> 00:40:40,240
It looks tasty. My goodness.

1240
00:40:40,380 --> 00:40:41,440
Thank you.

1241
00:40:41,680 --> 00:40:43,010
Thank you.

1242
00:40:43,150 --> 00:40:44,350
Woo Jin, what is it?

1243
00:40:44,710 --> 00:40:46,050
You look like a lost puppy.

1244
00:40:46,580 --> 00:40:48,350
(Teasing Woo Jin who can't eat ice cream)

1245
00:40:48,720 --> 00:40:50,190
Who ordered the basic one?

1246
00:40:50,190 --> 00:40:51,290
No, it's his.

1247
00:40:51,290 --> 00:40:52,790
- It's mine. - It isn't yours.

1248
00:40:52,790 --> 00:40:54,520
No, I ordered the chocolate one.

1249
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:55,890
Then... What?

1250
00:40:56,260 --> 00:40:58,490
- What's this? - He is eating more than us.

1251
00:40:58,490 --> 00:41:00,300
You ordered it when I said, "A regular one."

1252
00:41:00,430 --> 00:41:03,470
One chocolate one and two regular ones.

1253
00:41:03,470 --> 00:41:04,730
- What else? - A regular one.

1254
00:41:04,730 --> 00:41:06,440
(He approached Ji Sung and ordered regular ice cream.)

1255
00:41:06,940 --> 00:41:08,870
One regular one.

1256
00:41:09,070 --> 00:41:10,210
Jin Young doesn't want it.

1257
00:41:10,210 --> 00:41:11,270
Then we're set, right?

1258
00:41:11,270 --> 00:41:13,480
(Then he ordered a skewer.)

1259
00:41:13,910 --> 00:41:16,180
(At a distance, he saw that ice cream was being served.)

1260
00:41:16,180 --> 00:41:18,710
(Woo Jin)

1261
00:41:18,910 --> 00:41:21,120
(He returned to the ice cream store in the most natural way.)

1262
00:41:21,420 --> 00:41:24,690
- If you do that... - He is totally cunning.

1263
00:41:24,690 --> 00:41:26,160
(Thief Woo Jin's perfect crime leaves them speechless.)

1264
00:41:26,260 --> 00:41:27,360
Bye.

1265
00:41:27,790 --> 00:41:29,760
(Thanks for the snack.)

1266
00:41:30,030 --> 00:41:31,360
Aren't we going to the sea later?

1267
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:32,830
Why don't we push him in?

1268
00:41:33,230 --> 00:41:35,600
(He enjoys the skewer from Baby Bae as well.)

1269
00:41:36,730 --> 00:41:38,700
(He returns to the van with many snacks.)

1270
00:41:39,170 --> 00:41:40,400
Ji Sung is...

1271
00:41:41,270 --> 00:41:42,970
so good-natured and naive.

1272
00:41:44,040 --> 00:41:45,170
He is like that.

1273
00:41:45,540 --> 00:41:47,410
(Everyone becomes full during the Rest Area Time.)

1274
00:41:47,410 --> 00:41:50,710
(Team Fly to the Sky)

1275
00:41:50,950 --> 00:41:53,280
- The weather is so nice. - I know.

1276
00:41:53,280 --> 00:41:55,750
- Any aerial activity will be great. - I know.

1277
00:41:55,950 --> 00:41:59,620
I've always liked flying.

1278
00:41:59,960 --> 00:42:01,120
(Squirrel Ong loves flying...)

1279
00:42:01,120 --> 00:42:02,960
(and looking at the sky.)

1280
00:42:02,960 --> 00:42:04,830
(Seong Wu is a well-known flying squirrel.)

1281
00:42:04,960 --> 00:42:07,700
Did you go paragliding last time on "WANNA ONE GO?"

1282
00:42:07,700 --> 00:42:09,060
That's right.

1283
00:42:09,060 --> 00:42:10,730
(In the last season, he made a wish and tried paragliding.)

1284
00:42:10,730 --> 00:42:13,170
(The winking cutie loves activities.)

1285
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:16,610
You get goosebumps when you jump down yourself.

1286
00:42:16,770 --> 00:42:19,110
- It feels like the heart is here. - Yes.

1287
00:42:19,110 --> 00:42:20,780
It feels like it's getting separated.

1288
00:42:20,780 --> 00:42:21,780
It's like...

1289
00:42:21,780 --> 00:42:23,050
(Seong Wu's heart)

1290
00:42:23,050 --> 00:42:24,580
(Wasting his acting skills to explain)

1291
00:42:24,580 --> 00:42:25,980
(Absorbed)

1292
00:42:25,980 --> 00:42:27,820
